        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 3:12PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 311 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Benavides, moving northwest at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Diego, Freer, Premont, Benavides, Ramirez, San Jose, Concepcion,
Realitos, Palito Blanco, La Gloria, Bruni, Cruz Calle, Rios, and
Rosita.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
